The paper focuses on usability issues in open-source software and proposes a framework and automated technique for understanding and consolidating community opinions using argumentation models. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves content analysis and machine learning techniques for automated argument extraction, which are relevant to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the challenges of digesting information in issue tracking systems, which relates to the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a framework for effective discussion about usability, which is relevant to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
